ABOUT US ADMISSIONS QUICK FACTS TRANSFER DEGREES & COURSES Texas Christian University in Fort Worth, TX Research Texas Christian University. Read about its admission info, financial aid and bachelor's degree programs to make an informed education decision. About Texas Christian University Also known as TCU, this private university is located on 275 acres in downtown Fort Worth, Texas. Founded in 1873 and associated with the Christian Church (Disciples of Christ) denomination, TCU is ranked #97 among national universities by U.S. News & World Report rankings for 2012. Nicknamed the Horned Frogs, TCU joined the Big 12 varsity sports conference in July of 2012. The school colors are purple and white. Academics Texas Christian University has an enrollment of 9,518 students, of which 8,229 are undergraduates. TCU employs 532 faculty members full-time, of whom 87% have earned their terminal degree, and the student/faculty ratio is 13:1. TCU offers 131 different undergraduate majors divided into eight academic schools. Of these, the most renowned is the Neely School of Business, which is ranked by U.S. News & World Report at #69 among the best business programs for undergraduates in the country. Neely is also ranked highly by the Princeton Review and Bloomberg Businessweek. Areas of study at Neely School of Business include accounting, business, finance, information systems and supply chains, marketing, and management. Undergraduate students may earn the BBA. Other colleges at TCU include science and engineering, communications, education, and fine arts, as well as the AddRan College of Liberal Arts, and the Harris College of Nursing and Health Sciences. The John V. Roach Honors College offers outstanding juniors and seniors of every academic discipline the opportunity to enroll in courses that offer an intensive look at world cultures. Admissions TCU offers prospective freshmen the opportunity to apply online, using the school's own application form or a type of available form know as the Common Application. Incoming students must include the following additional elements to complete the application process: an essay, activities resume, evaluation from a high school guidance counselor, SAT or ACT scores, and a $40 admission fee. Students wishing to be considered for scholarships must also submit an evaluation by a teacher. Prospective students must submit their application by November 1 for early action and by December 15 to be eligible for scholarships. The final deadline is February 15. Tuition & Financial Aid Annual tuition at TCU costs $34,500, while room and board can cost another $10,650, and books run an additional $1,200 a year. Four different types of financial aid are available: scholarships, loans, grants, and work study. Approximately 79% of incoming freshman receive some kind of financial aid. Texas Christian University QUICK FACTS School Type Private, 4-year, University* Degrees Offered Certificate, bachelor's, master's, doctorate* Religious Affiliation Christian Church (Disciples of Christ)* Academic Calendar Semesters* School Setting Large city** Student Body 8,229 undergraduates and 1,289 graduates (2011)* ACADEMICS Schools (and/or) Programs Eight schools and colleges; 131 undergraduate degree programs* Student-Faculty Ratio 13:1* Most Popular Fields of Study by Degree Level (Number of Recipients) In 2010: Bachelor's: Registered Nursing/Registered Nurse (160) Master's: Business Administration and Management (118) Doctorate: Nursing Practice (21)** Undergraduate Graduation Rates 55% in four years 74% in six years 74% in 8 years** ADMISSIONS Admission Rate 38% in 2011** Entering Class Size 1,869 in 2011* First-Year Retention Rates 87% in 2011** Application Due Date February 15* Decision Notification Date April 1* TUITION & FINANCIAL AID Tuition (YEAR) $34,500* Financial Aid Sources Available (Percent of Students Receiving it) In 2011: Federal grants (15%), Pell grants (14%), other federal grants (11%), state and local grants/scholarships (16%), institutional grants/scholarships (67%), federal loans (37%)** Percent of Students Receiving Some Form of Aid 79%** Texas Christian University, **IPEDS Data Center, National Center for Education Statistics School Contact Information Address: Texas Christian University, 3301 Bellaire Dr. N., TCU Box 297013, Fort Worth, TX 76129 Phone: (817) 257-7490 Website: www.tcu.edu Get Admission Info Take the first step by getting admissions information directly from Texas Christian University. Simply answer a few questions to get started. What is your highest level of education? --- Select One --- High School / GED Associates Bachelor's Master's None of the above On average, people with a Bachelor's Degree earn 63% more than those with only a High School Diploma. (Source: BLS.gov 2012 ep) What subject area are you interested in? --- Select One --- Business Communications and Journalism Computer Sciences Education Engineering Legal Liberal Arts and Humanities Mechanic and Repair Technologies Medical and Health Professions Psychology Other In what year did you graduate high school? --- Select One --- Have not yet earned HS Diploma or GED 2015 2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 2004 2003 2002 2001 2000 1999 1998 1997 1996 1995 1994 1993 1992 1991 1990 1989 1988 1987 1986 1985 1984 1983 1982 1981 1980 1979 1978 1977 1976 1975 1974 1973 1972 1971 1970 or before Today I am interested in getting help from Study.com with: --- Select One --- Find jobs or prepare for an interview Improve my chances of getting accepted into school Find scholarships and grants I qualify for Get recommendations on schools to apply Match my interests with potential careers Read in depth comparisons of schools and careers Other None of the above Email: Zip Code: Your Name First Name: Last Name: 94% of college-bound high school students said it was important to communicate with colleges during the search process. (Source: Noel-Levitz 2012 trend study) Contact Informat